16. MS. in the library of the Earl of Leicester at Holkham, Norfolk. It is cited by Sir Frederic Madden in his glossary to Havelok, edited by him for the Roxburghe Club in 1828, as a Latin-English vocabulary of the middle of the fifteenth century, and substantially the same as the Ortus Vocalmlorum.a Chiefly on paper, partly on vellum. Its resemblance to the Medulla appears by extracts, for which I am indebted to the Rev. R. Collyer, Hon. Canon of Norwich.
